Module paceManager
Package data

Class Time

java.lang.Object
data.Time
public class Time
extends java.lang.Object
Stores the value of a given time. Value is stored as a long, specifying the time in ms.

Uses of stored time includes specifying a specific time and date, specifying a specific time of day, or specifying a difference in time

Since:
1.0.0
Version:
1.0.0
Author:
Thomas Kwashnak

    • value

      private final long value
      Value of Time stored as ms. The only way to specify this value is by creating a new Time using either Time() (sets value = 0) or Time(long) (allows for specification of value)

    • difference

      public static Time difference​(Time start, Time end)
      Calculates the difference between two Time objects.

      Will result in a Time object with negative values if the value of end is greater than the value of start

      Parameters:
      start - the first Time, typically less in value than end
      end - the second Time, typically greater in value than start
      Returns:
      A new Time object representing the difference between start and end
      Since:
      1.0.0
      See Also:
      value, absolute()

    • absolute

      public Time absolute()
      Returns a Time object with the positive value of value.

      For example, if value = -100, then will return a Time object with value = 100. Similarly, if value = 100, then will also return a Time object with value = 100.

      Returns:
      A new Time object with a positive value
      Since:
      1.0.0
